I have another weird thing: ForwardDiff seems super-slow, at the REPL, not the first run but every time:
```julia&gt; @time ForwardDiff.gradient(x -&gt; sum(x*x), rand(2,2));
  0.486069 seconds (4.17 M allocations: 220.887 MiB, 7.33% gc time, 99.86% compilation time)

julia&gt; @time Zygote.gradient(x -&gt; sum(x*x), rand(2,2));
  0.013145 seconds (33.95 k allocations: 1.881 MiB, 99.69% compilation time)

# but @btime is still fast:

julia&gt; @btime ForwardDiff.gradient(x -&gt; sum(x*x), $(rand(2,2)));
  317.021 ns (9 allocations: 1.02 KiB)

julia&gt; @btime Zygote.gradient(x -&gt; sum(x*x), $(rand(2,2)));
  546.319 ns (20 allocations: 1.02 KiB)```
Similar numbers with default terminal and iterm.

